A person who carries a biometric chip within their body that recieves and can transmit information such as the Verichip, [Media:[http//www.verichipcorp.com/], Texas Instruments [http//www.ti.com/rfid/docs/products/transponders/RI-TRP-BRHP.shtml] or similar type chips.  These type of chips can be read via satellite and the GVS registry and can also be read by your own computer (with the proper system devices included on your motherboard) and different types of RFID (Radio Frequency Identification) scanners [http//www.ti.com/rfid/docs/products/readers/readers.shtml]. 

Information that can be recieved include but is not limited to:  Heart rate, body temperature, blood pressure, and location coordinate of the individual. 

For a Photo see [www.biochipped.com]

This is technology currently being used but not being published as far as exactly how and why it can be used.  This type of implementation is limiltess.  The information that these chips can be used for is inhumane.